    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Burnley</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 28, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> On the 31st ultimo I had the honor to
                            bring to your notice the ease of Mr. Charles A. Russell, of the British
                            sloop Racer, captured off Bull’s bay, and to request that an
                            investigation of the matter might be made; and on the 3d instant you
                            informed me that a copy of my note had been transmitted to the Navy
                            Department.</p>
                <p>I shall be glad to learn how this affair now stands.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your most
                            obedient, humble servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. HUME BURNLEY.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>,<hi rend="italic">
                                    &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
